wikipedia_page.main: John Septimus Grover (30 October 1766 – 28 November 1852) was an English first-class cricketer with amateur status who was active in 1790. He was recorded playing for Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC) against Essex at Lord's Old Ground in May 1790, scoring 3 and 18 not out. He took 3 wickets in one innings, all bowled.
